DefaultEvent.Description: Tangy and toothsome. Walk on, chewing cheerfully.
DefaultEvent.Name: Not bad at all

ChildBranches.Name: Try the grilled troglodyte prawns
ChildBranches.Description: Huge and pale, and their eyes stare bleakly into yours. But they smell fresh.

DefaultEvent.Description: Now satisfied. How rich and red.
DefaultEvent.Name: That particular hunger

ChildBranches.Name: "Do you have anything more... robust?"
ChildBranches.Description: The vendor winks, and produces a usefully anonymous skewer of meat.

SuccessEvent.Description: Tyrant-moth antennae! You know how to deal with these. You break it into fragments and swallow the dripping fragments each in a gulp, exhaling briskly to savour the vapours afterwards. It's a complex rather than a pleasant flavour, but its tonic effects are marvellous.
SuccessEvent.Name: Rare and delicious!

DefaultEvent.Description: You follow the vendor's advice, holding your nose as you swallow, but the smell - something like rotting fruit - still makes you gag. The 'stick' is leathery - the blue stuff is rubbery as drying mucus. You fail to keep it down, and disgrace your captaincy there on the street.
DefaultEvent.Name: Hold your nose

ChildBranches.Name: Try something mysterious
ChildBranches.Description: What exactly is 'tyrant's treat'? The vendor is vague. It looks something like a charred stick dripping with bluish fluid.

SuccessEvent.Description: Traces of its venom still remain - just enough to make your tongue tingle and alter your consciousness a touch. Your pulse accelerates, and odd thoughts sparkle in the forefront of your mind.
SuccessEvent.Name: Jillyfish: the food of queens

DefaultEvent.Description: Urgh. You'll regret it later. The jillyfish's venom numbs your tongue and roils your stomach.
DefaultEvent.Name: Force it down

Description: "Who'll try? Who'll buy?" A street-vendor turns skewers on a grill. The mixed scents are nothing like anything sold in London.
Name: An Intriguing Smell
